
HOWTO EDIT WIKI CALENDAR VIA GIT/GITHUB
==========================================================


1

If you've never edited the calendar before, first clone the wiki pages to
create folder nysc.wiki:

  % git clone git@github.com:tintinnabuli/nysc.wiki.git


If you're returning to an existing sandbox to update the calendar, pull the
wiki repo to make sure you're up to date:

  % cd nysc.wiki
  % git pull



2

To edit and update the calendar:

  % ...edit calendar.md...
  % git add calendar.md
  % git commit
  % git push



3

The proof your changes on the web:

  https://github.com/tintinnabuli/nysc/wiki/calendar




#----------------------------------------- -o-
USING MARKDOWN

Files ending in *.md can contain markdown directives.


Markdown is a simple as pie.  Here's a cheatsheet:
  
  http://scottboms.com/downloads/documentation/markdown_cheatsheet.pdf


Here's the primary source:

  http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown

